==English==

===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[arbiter]]'' - eye-witness, on-looker; judge, overseer, lord; executor. Mainly in legal context.

===Pronunciation===
*{{italbrac|[[RP]]}} {{IPA|/ˈɑːbɪtrəri/}}
*{{italbrac|US}} {{IPA|/ˈɑːrbɪtrɛri/}}
*{{audio|en-us-arbitrary.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Determined by [[impulse]] rather than [[reason]].
# Chosen for no reason or at [[random]]. 
#: ''The equation is true for an '''arbitrary''' value of x.''

====Usage notes====
*Something is arbitrary if its value is not determined by anything but choice.

